rComments: Very little course material and a LOT of assigned readings. Exams are very long and the required answers tenuous, total regurgitation of the reading material with little to no room for critical thinking. Strict grader. Very low effort class on behalf of the prof yet extensive towards students. Without a doubt the most difficult course I've taken.

Instead of the 6 hours of lecture we were supposed to get a week, she records 20-30 minutes of scripted Powerpoints and assigns 100 pages of readings plus documentaries to watch. Not sure why I had to pay to teach myself the class. Definitely would not recommend.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: I WOULD RATE ZERO IF I CAN. This professor posted mark nearly the last day of the semester. I can not even select the satisfactory grade. AND YOU DONT EVEN KNOW YOUR GRADE UNTIL THE LAST MINUTE. AVOID HER.

Her class is wasting time. She expects you to answer 10 long questions in 90 minutes. And gave you few marks. Also, I got my previous exam marks on the final exam period. I've taken Professor Coucopoulos's CRIM 1700 class over the summer and online, and I would NOT recommend it... The class content was not hard, but the mid term and group paper were challenging. The mid terms are based on the lectures (30 mins/ week) AND readings (A LOT). You must write literally everything you know about the topic to do well. I find midterms are more regurgitation than explanation/ knowledge. A challenging course for sure.

unaccommodating. There was a lack of drive and I felt no effort on her end. I am currently in this prof's class and I have no kind words. She only grades three things, two midterms (25% each with one in early February and the other in late March) and a final (50%). I am yet to receive my mark for my second midterm as of April 17 meaning that I am in exam season only knowing 25% of my overall grade. The stress is real! SOS

i've heard bad things about Zoi, but her online lectures are super good. its supposed to be a 3 hour lecture, but she only does a 25 minute recording, and assigns a few more readings. open book midterm that was pretty simple, along with a group paper where you can chose your own topic (but she choses the group). the course is interesting too

This is my first time giving a rating for a professor. This is not a joke. FEM2507A is my first uni failure and i highly recommend to avoid Coucopolous if you're trying to get good grades. This is not a joke please be aware.

Prof reads off her powerpoint for the whole period. Tests have very specific questions about the classes and the textbook. Do not take this class is you have difficulty remembering everything by heart. Powerpoints aren't posted online.

Easy A+. Th only annoying part is the long readings that are usually irrelevant. Take really good notes (her slides are not available to the students) and learn for the exams. - examens pas conformes au contenu du cours - lectures qui ne sont "soit disant" pas obligatoires mais qui tombent dans l'examen - lectures INTROUVABLES sur brightspace - matière inintéressante qui ne contient que des énumérations - se réserve le droit de ne pas répondre à des questions qu'elle trouve "inadéquate" - aucune contextualisation
